1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,950
What if a liquidity pool could play the
World Cup?

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:11,971
This is Mundial — a Uniswap v4 hook on X
Layer. It doesn't pick one match or trust

3
00:00:12,021 --> 00:00:17,450
an admin. It runs the entire tournament —
with no one in charge.

4
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:23,956
Fans pledge one of eight teams — once,
irreversibly. When their team's match is

5
00:00:24,006 --> 00:00:30,709
live, every swap becomes a shot on goal.
Volume scores goals. The market plays the

6
00:00:30,759 --> 00:00:31,450
football.

7
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:42,950
Watch it run. Argentina versus France —
fans trade, goals go up.

8
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:47,450
Five to three — Argentina advance.

9
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:55,237
Brazil against England is scoreless into
extra time. One Brazilian fan swaps…

10
00:00:55,287 --> 00:00:56,450
GOLDEN GOAL.

11
00:00:56,500 --> 00:01:00,450
The match settles inside the very swap
that scored it.

12
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:05,959
Semifinals, penalties decided by shot
counts, a final — and a champion is

13
00:01:06,009 --> 00:01:08,450
crowned. All of it, hook storage.

14
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:16,379
One dynamic-fee pool. Fans pay lower fees
— a quarter percent, dropping to

15
00:01:16,429 --> 00:01:20,450
point-one-five while their team plays.

16
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:26,000
A zero-point-two percent skim builds the
Champions Pot. Winning fans claim it

17
00:01:26,050 --> 00:01:28,450
pro-rata; leftovers go to the LPs.

18
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:36,339
No owner. No oracle. No randomness. The
only inputs are swaps and time.

19
00:01:36,389 --> 00:01:39,450
Seventy-seven tests. Fuzzed.

20
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:47,450
Deployed on X Layer. Code public on
GitHub.

21
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:53,450
Mundial. Live on X Layer. The pool that
plays the World Cup.

